i think I fell in love with flying 😍 The feeling you get when you’re up in the air cannot be explained. You have to experience it for yourself, feel it with your heart and soul to understand it. It’s simply indescriptable. I’ve never felt so free and happy. It’s beautiful and insane at the same time. It’s peaceful and exciting all at once. It’s like the missing piece you didn’t know you need it. It’s like a pause in this very complex and intense world. A moment of pure joy where everything is put aside and where the present moment is all that matters. 

Iykyk

social_posts.post_text: If it was perfect it wouldn’t be real 🦋

Grateful for the friends I’ve made along the way 💗  I don’t have it all figured it out and sometimes (often) my life feels like a mess. But at least I have friends I can count on ❤️ 

(also @cossette.en knows how to party 😂🎉)
making memories that will last a lifetime 😌

I never thought I would find the desire to write again. But here it is, as I stand at the top of the CN tower and look at the view of what used to be home.

This summer was nothing like what I had expected. It was billion times better. In the midst of all the craziness and moments with my friends who became like a second family, I thought to myself… Maybe I do have something beautiful to share with the world. Maybe I can start writing again. 💗

I wanted to write “catching flights not feelings” but I did catch feelings for 🇫🇷 during this trip so now I’ve ran out of words 🌝

France • Part 1

I never thought I would experience what I experienced during this trip. It was definitely one of the most beautiful and memorable moment of my life. 

It was everything I needed. And without a doubt, I can say that things worked out just the way they were supposed to. I wouldn’t have it any another way. See you later, France. 🇫🇷

France • Part 2

This year was by far the most beautiful and insane year of my life 🤍

The people I’ve meet, the places I’ve seen, the things I have discovered…

There’s nothing I wouldn’t change because it has made me who I am today.

I’m so grateful! Bye bye 2023 🫶
Through every laugh, tear, and adventure, friends become the family we choose. Grateful for these bonds that go beyond blood. 🩵
